The Federal Government is set to shut the Third Mainland Bridge for six months starting from Friday, July 24, 2020.<img src="https://i2.wp.com/instablog9ja.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instablog9ja_20200706_20.jpg?resize=922%2C922" /> “We want to do maintenance work on Third Mainland Bridge very soon.We may close it from 24th of July.We are still working out the modalities and when we perfect the traffic management plan we will move to site. Everything being expected for the repairs of the bridge arrived the country, that is why we want to start the repairs now,” he said. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.